text: Jihlava () is a city in the Czech Republic. It is the capital of the Vysočina Region. In 2020, 51,216 people lived there. The city is on the Jihlava river () on the historical border between Moravia and Bohemia. It is the oldest mining town in the country. == References == Category:Cities in the Czech Republic Category:Vysočina Region
